result.execSummary:
Tuffy Brian Schulz was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Tuffy Brian Schulz was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Tuffy Brian Schulz in court.  Frederick j Schellgell appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA calls case, cites appearances.  Right to attorney explained.  Clerk to provide Public Def information.  Defendant agrees to return to MN.  States he knows what is all about.  Defendant doesn't want to have an attorney.  Freely waives right to counsel.  Waives extradition and signs waiver/consent.  Court also signs Waiver and Consent.  Adj. 11:38 a.m.  klr
